rComments: he should not be teaching first years. just reads off slides

This man is the reason I changed my major. He gave literally no help to anyone that asked and was extremely rude to me whenever I went up to him to ask a question. He only let the same three people talk and seemed annoyed when anyone else offered input. He made me hate political science.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Tough grader']

rComments: I hated this class! His lectures are long and boring! Avoid him if you want to enjoy your political science class. He is knowledgeable,  but boring. He grades really fairly though! If you put in the effort on the assignments you'll do well. DGDs are a part pf your grade, and so is the twitter discussion which is very confusing,
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'So many papers']

rComments: OVeral a really nice guy.  Very approachable and helpful in office hours.  However classes are quite dull and he reads directly off of the slides most of the time.  A few long papers with vague expectations.

Excellent Professor. Very considerate and approachable, had reasonable expectations and workload, lectured with clarity and depth. No real complaints on my part. Definitely good to take if you are familiar with and into political science as he is one of the best in the department at teaching higher level concepts effectively.

By far the best prof i've had at the University level. Unreal guy, so knowledgable and always there to help before or after class. If you show an interest and are a genuine person he'll respond positively. Very humble guy willing to go out of his way to help his students!

Very sweet prof. Really wants to help his students -- before the exam, he even had a slide titled "Dad stuff", giving us tips on what to do before the exam (like sleep, eat well, etc.). Sometimes he mumbles, or perhaps it's just the accent!
not the best lecturer, fairly average, however nice professor, ask for help especially for your first poli sci course

Nice guy but, very monotone. Didn't explain a lot and read directly off his slides. Didn't learn anything this semester & would not recommend taking his class. Obviously very knowledgeable but, unable to convey the material to the class the T.A was better at explaining the material.

This prof is obviously intelligent and a good guy but not very good at conveying material. This was supposed to be an intro class but he expected his students to have vast background knowledge in politics. The class was incredibly dull and entirely political theory. Almost half the class ended up dropping the course, likely you will too.

The class itself was interesting and well rounded. However, as a teacher, not so much. It's clear that he's very intelligent and he knows what he's talking about but he doesn't know how to make a class engaging and he mumbles A LOT. I barely understood him. It's hard to want to go to class. He's a nice guy though and the DGDs helped some.
very dull, reads off the slides and doesnt really elaborate on his points. I was very disappointed in this course.

He is a great, and I definitely recommend him. He is incredibly intelligent, funny, & nice. Course load is heavy for first year, and but it pays off. Can be difficult because he teaches the class to a high level. Bases class off of course-pack readings which you must do to understand the lecture. Very helpful outside of class, and understanding.

This class is understandable and he provides lots of examples when he explains his ideas. Here is some advice, his slides actually don't mean anything unless you also listen to the teacher explaining the points on the slides. :)

The assignments are very vague. He is a really nice man though, and definitely knows what he's talking about. My advice is GO TO THE DGDs, you cover a lot of material and it really helps to clarify and organize it all.
Fav Prof
Great Professor!
Really interesting class. Has a cool British accent. Very nice and funny. Always helpful during office hours!
horrible accent, boring lectures, uses too many complex words for a first year class, very hard to follow, not looking forward to this class

He's a really nice guy, and obviously smart... But really shouldn't be teaching a first year class.  His lectures were unorganized and boring.  I don't think he completed a lecture in a single class ever.  His assignments were outstandingly vague and broad.  I really love POL but hated this class unfortunately.
Always has a lot to say.  Nice guy, interesting lectures

He teaches a great course, but prepare to do lots of readings. He's not out to make students fail; he wants to make them learn. So he clearly explains assignments and even gives the exam questions ahead of time. He's a very clear, concise lecturer, and you'll learn a lot in his course.

i found him incredibly difficult to understand. at the end of each lecture i coudln't tell you what he lectured on. so come exam, i had to teach myself the whole course. thank god he gave us the exam ahead of time. paper was marked incredibly easy. worst paper of my life and i got an A. probably smart if i could understand him. lotts of reading, an

He knows his stuff!!  The lectures are a bit scattered at times but they are fun.  The reading are too heavy though.  If you have time for his office hours, you should go.  He is very easy to talk you and a nice guy.  I bet he knows his ratings ;-)
Very knowledgeable prof. Hard but fair marker and very helpful during office hours.  Only had one class with him so far, but will hopefully have more in the future.

Most students didn't go to lectures since he posts notes online. He is hard to understand at times because he mumbles and trails off. The class was boring. Good thing is he gave the exam out weeks in advance. I wouldn't recommend this course to someone who isn't really interested in poli sci. Too much work & dull.

The most challanging class I have ever taken, quite possibly because the prof. is incredibly difficult to follow. Grammatical clash between european and canadian english... still very well read and incredibly intelligent.
Great proffessor. The marking is tough - but not unreasonable. The workload was heavy, but again not unreasonable at all. It is tough to sit through a 3 hour evening class.

The workload is way too much for a second year course.  He is a really nice guy, but the structure of the class is innapropriate for such a large group, (dividing 150 ppl up to do 5 minute dicussions) there are 3 or 4 TA's who do the marking in addition to him and the marks are all skewed, so basically your mark is dependant on which TA you get.

Seems like a nice guy but extremely hard marker. First class I've ever had to drop because it was just getting depressing - my grade was 20% lower than in any of my other courses. Good at encouraging discussion and extremely knowledgeable on the subject matter though.

The workload was heavier in this class than any of my others. He's a fair marker. A real nice guy who is genuinely concerned about his students. Sometimes it was difficult to follow him because of his mumbling.
He is one of the nicest profs at the awful school.  He marks fairly and is always willing to help students.  It's a very boring class, but he is super super nice

Great guy and great prof. Gives exams weeks in advance and seems to be a fair marker. I don't think I've stayed for a whole lecture yet though (year long course, too) and I'm pulling off somewhere between a B+ and A-.
He is sooo hot! Sexy British accent makes me swoon. He's the cutest guy ever, and the best prof ever. I want him all to myself.
A nice guy and mostly good prof, except for his poor ability to engage students in subject matter.
Wonderful teacher.  Extremely helpful and sympathetic to students.  A breath of fresh air compared to most profs.  Excellent grip over the English language which is at a premium at this school!
The material wasn't engaging enough to make stay for a full lecture. He's a smart guy though and should be given more credit.
You'll have to work hard to get A's in this class but always seems to be willing to help and is very approachable.
He mumbles a bit, but overall, good guy, good prof.  approachable and quick to clarify, if need be

A really engaging prof, class discussions always fun and educational. Grading on work can be harsh if he uses TA's, but he's really fair himself. I love the British accent, and he's a total cutie. Smat, cute, and funny, in other words the perfect man... I mean prof. hehe
